Our County’s move to Phase 2, announced by @GovRonDeSantis, lifts a roadblock that prevented us from taking steps to reopen schools. With guidance from medical experts & the School Board, we're optimistic that we'll be able to make an announcement prior to Sept. 30, as planned. Our schools will have additional health and safety protocols in place ahead of students returning. As we previously shared, there will be choice in our District for those parents who opted to continue remote learning during Phase 2. #MDCPSReopening

post_text:
Recognizing the technical difficulties many students, teachers & parents experienced with K-12 platform, effective immediately, based on School Board action on Sept. 9, all teachers will connect w/ students through Microsoft Teams or Zoom through Microsoft Teams. Instructions below.
******
Debido a las dificultades técnicas que muchas familias y maestros han tenido con la plataforma K12, efectivo inmediatamente, según la acción de la Junta Escolar del 9/9, los maestros se conectarán con estudiantes a través de Microsoft Teams o Zoom a través de Microsoft Teams.
******
Nan rekonèt difikilte teknik anpil elèv, pwofesè ak paran te rankontre ak platfòm K12, efektif imedyatman, baze sou aksyon Komisyon Konsèy Lekòl 9 septanm, tout pwofesè pral kòmanse konekte ak elèv atravè ‘Microsoft Teams’ oubyen ‘Zoom’ atravè ‘Microsoft Teams’.

shared_text:
Alberto Carvalho
July 29 at 10:32 PM ·

We are ever-cognizant that many families have already begun planning for a return to schooling through their preferred model for Stage 2. However, in light of the viral surge in our community, we believe it is in the best interest of our students and employees to delay the return to the schoolhouse and commence the 2020-2021 school year from a distance. Beginning the week of August 24, we will engage families, students, and teachers in a week of learning and orientation.

We stand committed and prepared to deliver to our community
that which they have come to expect from us, a world-class educational experience. During these unprecedented times for school systems across the nation, rest assured that Miami-Dade County Public Schools is ready to Reopen Smart & Return Safe. To view the latest #MDCPSReopening plan, visit http://reopening.dadeschools.net/.

shared_text:
Alberto Carvalho
July 1 at 10:12 PM ·

Over the past several months, our nation and community have been responding to an unprecedented crisis as a result of #COVID19. With a high level of preparation and the foresight of the School Board and leadership team, we have been engaged in the challenging task of planning for the reopening of schools this fall. As we developed this plan, we established a workgroup comprised of leaders in our community and medical experts who provided guidance critical to informing our practices, as we face a virus associated with significant unknowns and ever‐changing circumstances. The workgroup gave unanimous support to the proposed #MDCPSReopening plan, which is comprehensive in nature and incorporates guidance from national, state and local experts. This plan hinges on conditions in the local community & whether or not Miami-Dade County Government is in Phase 2 of reopening according to The Plan for Florida’s Recovery.
text:
Alberto Carvalho
July 1 at 10:12 PM ·

Over the past several months, our nation and community have been responding to an unprecedented crisis as a result of #COVID19. With a high level of preparation and the foresight of the School Board and leadership team, we have been engaged in the challenging task of planning for the reopening of schools this fall. As we developed this plan, we established a workgroup comprised of leaders in our community and medical experts who provided guidance critical to informing our practices, as we face a virus associated with significant unknowns and ever‐changing circumstances. The workgroup gave unanimous support to the proposed #MDCPSReopening plan, which is comprehensive in nature and incorporates guidance from national, state and local experts. This plan hinges on conditions in the local community & whether or not Miami-Dade County Government is in Phase 2 of reopening according to The Plan for Florida’s Recovery.

Affirming decency, advocating for justice and equality for all, while standing firm in our values, should never result in condemnation by anyone who believes in the true power of the beautifully diverse community we are. There is unity in community but only if we compassionately, empathetically, and honestly listen to one another while never distorting what we know, hear, see, or read. The School Board of Miami-Dade County stands for and advocates for the best interests of our children and the community we serve; always has and always will.
